  "function_path": "sklearn/decomposition/_fastica.py",
  "function_name": "_fit_transform",
  "justification": "This method of the FastICA class performs the core ICA fitting procedure. It takes a 2D array of shape (n_samples, n_features) and a boolean compute_sources flag. It validates and transposes input data, selects nonlinearity functions (logcosh, exp, cube, or custom), determines n_components by clamping to min(samples, features), optionally performs whitening with centering and eigendecomposition/SVD (lines 607-639), initializes the unmixing matrix randomly (lines 645-657), delegates to _ica_par for parallel decorrelation or _ica_def for deflation algorithms (lines 667-670), and computes separated sources if requested (lines 675-689). It returns either None or an array of shape (n_samples, n_components), and as a side effect sets instance attributes: components_, mixing_ (pseudo-inverse), mean_, whitening_, _unmixing (weight matrix), and n_iter_ (iteration count) - lines 673, 691-698."
}

